description:
The loading and off -loading of air cargo in and out of International
Airports Designated as Ports of Entry is permitted. Air cargo from medium to high risk countries must be sanitised immediately after being off- loaded from the aircraft.
The following International Airports Designated as Ports of Entry have 
Port Health capability and are ready to handle air cargo and services:
(a) O.R Tambo;
(b) King Shaka;
(c) Upington;
(d) Polokwane;
(e) Bram Fischer;
(f) Kruger Mpumalanga;
(g) Pilanesberg;
(h) Port Elizabeth; and
(i) Cape Town.

Prasa will continue with the maintenance, servicing and testing of its fleet and further sanitise and disinfect its stations and hubs and on completion must announce the resumption of the following commuter services:
(a) Pienaarspoort to Pretoria Central;
(b) Cape Town Southern line to Simonstown;
(c) East London to Berlin;
(d) Port Elizabeth to Uitenhage; and
(e) Any other commuter services.

Gautrain will continue commuter services as follows:
(a) Park Station to Hatfield; and
(b) Sandton to OR Tambo international Airport.

The government of South Africa has imposed a ban on international travel  under special circumstances from 1st of June under level 3 lockdown protocol while informing citizens that they must, at least five working days in advance of the intended date of travel, provide the Department of Home Affairs with the following documentation:

-A copy of his or her valid South African passport;
-A letter of confirmation of admissibility or the validity of the visa or permit, issued by the relevant diplomatic or consular mission or authority of the receiving country;
-Where transiting through another country, proof of permission to transit through such country;
-Proof of the means of travel and the intended date of departure.
